reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Lovely - Beautiful - Assembly Snafu
reviews.reviewText: This is a lovely piece of furniture. Laminate on MDF is often very meh, but this one is done quite nicely. It looks like real, high quality wood with the rattan adding a tropical vibe. Boxed arrived with all parts in perfect condition.Assembly is easier than most, taking about one hour. The directions are very clear, except for step 4 where the bottom is attached. The drawings shows 4 long wood screws (J) going into the bottom board (4). In the drawing only one possible set of holes for the screws (J) are shown on the side panels (2 & 3), but in reality there are two sets to choose from. I choose incorrectly and had to go back and correct it later. When you get to that point, choose the larger of the holes. Another way is to take one of the legs (part 8) and line it up across the holes in question. It will reveal which set of holes goes with the legs, and which goes with the bottom board.Other than that little detour, assembly was a breeze. I also love their door hinge scheme which eschews typical hinges that are a pain to install. Their door hinges are much easier and foolproof.Only other nitpick is the shelf could be more stable.All of that said, this is an excellent sideboard buffet cabinet. Very sturdy, genuinely high quality materials, and looks fantastic. Highly recommended.I hope this review was helpful, thank you for reading.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great entryway table
reviews.reviewText: This table is extremely easy to put together. I also love that the legs are metal because sometimes the cheaper furniture has thin wood legs that break easily. The shelves can be adjusted to whatever height you like which is a must! The only thing that doesn’t look expensive is the knobs but for this price point can’t complain!
